{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Trail"], "type": "title", "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "text": ["Creates trails behind points."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["The Trail op takes an input op and makes a trail of each point of the\ninput op over the past several frames, and connects the trails in\ndifferent ways. It will generate trails of any input geometry, whether\nit is a cube translating, a deforming surface, or particles. This is\nuseful for multi-frame ghosting effects and temporal modeling."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["When using a ", {"text": ["Particle SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/particle", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/particle"}, " or ", {"text": ["Spring\nSOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/spring", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/spring"}, " as input, it is important to keep the trail\nincrement to integer values. Otherwise, the trail will not work well."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["The particles thrown off the end-most points receive a higher\n        velocity than those close to the root of the L-system (enable\n        Points display in Viewport Display):"]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/images/TrailSOP-Example.jpg", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "../images/TrailSOP-Example.jpg"}]}], "indent": 4, "level": 3, "text": ["Velocity Computation"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Temporal modeling with the Trail op: the corners of a\n        translated and rotated cube are used as a source for the Trail\n        op with a ", {"text": ["Trail Length"], "type": "em"}, " of 50 frames connected by ", {"text": ["Columns"], "type": "em"}, "."]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/images/Houdini-03-1-082.jpg", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "../images/Houdini-03-1-082.jpg"}]}], "indent": 4, "level": 3, "text": ["Temporal Modeling"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Examples"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["How to construct the trail geometry."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Result Type"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Number of frames in trail."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Trail Length"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/length"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Number of frames to skip in trail."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Trail Increment"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/inc"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Number of frames to cache in RAM."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Cache Size"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/cache"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Resets the cache memory buffer."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Reset Cache"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Clamp evaluation between ", {"text": ["$FSTART"], "type": "code"}, " and ", {"text": ["$FEND"], "type": "code"}, ", otherwise may\n        evaluate before start frame."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Evaluate Within Frame Range"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["How to create the output mesh."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Connectivity"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Closes the rows in the output mesh."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Close Rows"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["When computing velocity the resulting velocity will be scaled by this\n        constant.  Note there is an internal scale of ", {"text": ["$FPS"], "type": "code"}, " to convert the\n        measured change over a frame into a change over a second."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Velocity Scale"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/velscale"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["This is the method that is used to approximate the velocity from the\n        point positions."]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["You can choose between ", {"text": ["Backward Difference"], "type": "ui"}, ", ", {"text": ["Central\n        Difference"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Forward Difference"], "type": "ui"}, ". Generally, ", {"text": ["Central\n        Difference"], "type": "ui"}, " gives more accurate results."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Velocity Approximation"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/velapproximation"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["The difference in orientation of successive frames will be used to\n        compute an angular velocity, ", {"text": ["w"], "type": "code"}, ", for the points."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "text": ["The ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, " attribute is needed to compute angular velocity. Without ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, ", the angular velocities are all zero."]}], "indent": 8, "role": "item", "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Compute Angular Velocity"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Points on successive frames will be identified by using the provided\n        integer attribute rather than the point number."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Match by Attribute"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["The name of the integer or string point attribute to use for matching\n        successive frames."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Attribute to Match"]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cache", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/cache"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/timeshift", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/timeshift"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Creates trails behind points."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "anim, time, tech", "namespace": null, "internal": "trail", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/trail"}, "title": ["Trail"]}